Rating: 4
I have been looking for a good chocolate bread pudding recipe for a long time and this is it. Very easy to make. I also thought the butter dots were unnecessary and didn't use them the second time I made the recipe with no problem. I used Ghirardelli bittersweet chocolate. I love dark chocolate but others might have preferred some semi-sweet mixed in as it is not overly sweet. Good quality bread is a must. The bread mixture needs to be soaked long enough so that the bread is soaked through, otherwise there are white flecks of bread when it is served. I tossed a handful of Ghirardelli Double Chocolate Chips on top and it was excellent. This recipe is a keeper.

