Rating: 3
I don't usually make anything this calorie-intensive, so I decided to tart it up a bit. Added a tablespoon of orange zest and a generous splash of Grand Marnier with the vanilla... also Ghirardelli only makes bittersweet chocolate in 4 oz bars, so I went for broke and used 12 oz chocolate instead of 10. The result was incredibly yummy -- not too sweet, very chocolatey, and rich as Croesus. I won't be making this again anytime soon, as my arteries need at least a year to recover, but this recipe is definitely super-tasty.